page.title: 12HERRINGTHORPE WOODS ROTH'HAM
page.content: My friend and I are keen bird watchers,My garden has a gate that leads into the Herringthorpe woods and into Gibbings Greave woods.There are lots of wood pigeons or ring necked doves and there are a variety of magpies. Also there a lot of starlings and a lot of sparrows,there are a lot of blue tits which collect the hair when we groom our dog to build their nest.In winter there are many robins in the woods.In the summer Herringthorpe woods are very beautiful and in the Autumn we go chesnut collecting.There used to be squirrels in the wood,but not any more
